quran[19]{c,v,t,f}:
73,1,"O you the (sleeping) enwrapped one! {1}",footnotes:1:To address the Prophet (peace be upon him) with these words and then to command him to rise and keep standing in the Prayer at night
73,2,"Stand up in Prayer by night, all but a small part of it; {1}",footnotes:1:This can have two meanings:
73,3,"half of it, or reduce it a little;"
73,4,"or add to it a little; {1} and recite the Qur'an slowly and distinctly. {2}",footnotes:1:This is an explanation of the duration of time commanded to be spent in worship. In it the Prophet (peace be upon him) was given the option to spend half of the night in the Prayer
73,5,"Behold, We shall cast upon you a Weighty Word. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
73,6,"Surely getting up at night {1} is the best means of subduing the self {2} and is more suitable for uprightness in speech. {3}",footnotes:1:About the meaning of the word nashiat allail
73,7,"You are indeed much occupied during the day with the affairs of the world."
73,8,"So remember the name of your Lord {1} and devote yourself to Him with exclusive devotion.",footnotes:1:After making mention of the occupation of the daytime
73,9,"He is the Lord of the East and the West; there is no god but He. So take Him alone for your Guardian, {1}",footnotes:1:Wakil is a person in whom one has complete faith; so much so that one can entrust all his affairs to him with full satisfaction of the heart. Thus
73,10,"And bear patiently the vain things they utter, and gracefully {1} forsake them.",footnotes:1:Depart from them does not mean break off all ties with them and stop preaching to them
73,11,"Leave it to Me to deal with the affluent ones who give the lie {1} (to the Truth), and bear with them for a while.",footnotes:1:These words clearly contain the sense that the people
73,12,"We have heavy fetters {1} and a blazing Fire in store for them;",footnotes:1:Heavy shackles in Hell will not be put on the criminals’ feet to stop them from escape but in order that they are not able to stand up and move; these will not be used to prevent their escape but as an instrument of their torment.
73,13,"and a food that chokes, and a grievous chastisement."
73,14,"(They will come across all this) on the Day when the earth and the mountains shall tremble violently and the mountains shall crumble into heaps of scattered sand. {1}",footnotes:1:Since at that time the cohesive force to bind the parts of the mountains together will cease to work
73,15,"Surely {1} We have sent to you a Messenger as a witness over you, {2} just as We had sent a Messenger to Pharaoh.",footnotes:1:The address now turns to the disbelievers of Makkah
73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed Our Messenger, so We seized him with a terrible seizing."
73,17,"If you persist in disbelieving, how will you guard yourself against the (woe of the) Day that will turn children grey-haired, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
73,18,"the Day whose severity shall cause the heaven to split asunder? Allah's promise is ever bound to be fulfilled."
73,19,"Indeed this is nothing but a Good Counsel; so let him who will take a way leading to his Lord."
